problem:
Find the number of ordered triples $(x,y,z)$ of real numbers such that
\begin{align*}
x + 2y + 4z &= 12, \\
xy + 2xz + 4yz &= 22, \\
xyz &= 6.
\end{align*}

Solve the following system of equations, where \(a, b, c, d\) are distinct real parameters:

\[
\begin{aligned}
x + y + z & = 1 \\
a x + b y + c z & = d \\
a^{2} x + b^{2} y + c^{2} z & = d^{2}
\end{aligned}
\]

ground_truth_answer:
\begin{aligned}
x &= \frac{(d - c)(b - d)}{(a - c)(b - a)} \\
y &= \frac{(a - d)(c - d)}{(b - a)(b - c)} \\
z &= \frac{(a - d)(d - b)}{(a - c)(c - b)}
\end{aligned}
